name: Spaghetti Squash Dip
author: HOLLYG1
summary: This is a great alternative to a spinach-artichoke dip. Instead of using fresh spinach, this is an even tastier combination. Serve it hot with tortilla chips or crackers.
ingredients: 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese for topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place the spaghetti squash cut side down on a lightly greased baking sheet
Place in preheated oven, and bake until soft when a fork is inserted
Scoop out the cooked squash, and place in a mixing bowl
Add butter to the squash and stir until butter melts
Stir the mayonnaise, 1 cup Parmesan cheese, and Monterey Jack cheese into the squash mixture until well blended
Pour into the prepared baking dish
Bake in preheated oven until cheese melts, about 20 minutes
